label act1:
    scene bg snowy with fade
    "A warm breath puffs up through my chest and out of my lips, being born into the world as a soft whisp in the frigid February air."
    "I hadn't noticed it before, but a soft flutter of a hand through my straight flaxen blonde hair disturbs the dusting of little white flakes which had begun to collect there."
    C "And now it's snowing too. Wonderful."
    "A frown solidly on my face, I hump the duffle strap more securely over my shoulder as I continue down the long wooded path toward my new academy."
