    rm "A better introduction than {b}this{/b}. How silly of me to have fallen asleep..."
    "My heart skips a beat as I watch her suffer my rude greeting after having gone to such lengths to welcome me into the room she lives in."
    "Struggling to find the right balance of apologizing and keeping my distance, I brush a hand through my own fair tresses in a show of casual detachment."
    C "Sorry, I was just surprised to hear you, and I'm super late, and sore from lugging my bag all the way here, and the two crazy girls touched me all over, and..."
    "I surprise even myself by beginning to stumble over my apologies, and by how sharply I am watching her pretty face for any signs of her coming around."
    "Why I care so much about her feelings, I don't know, but I rationalize that it's better to be on her good side than her bad."
