scene woolsey_intro:
    scene bg black with fade
    scene bg dormitory with dissolve
    "We find Miss Woolsey's door quickly enough. As it turns out, Sibyl only has to lead me to the end of the floor to find her room."
    "She knocks, but we receive no answer."
    S "Hmmm."
    "I wait patiently beside Sibyl, observing the confused thoughts play through her head as they are shown upon her profile."
    S "She's usually here by this time."
    "It's only when she turns her head to speak back in my direction that I realize how much I've been staring and stumble to quickly reply."
    C "Maybe she's gone out? We should just go back to our room."
    S "Some people get cranky when they're hungry, Clover."
    "I can only imagine this ambiguously worded statement is directed at my earlier performance, and shut myself up as the guilty party here while I think of another way out of this."
    who "Sorry girls, I had an important meeting."
    "At the sound of another arrival behind us, I know my doom is fully sealed and that there's no escape."
    "The woman who comes up behind us I find to look like the textbook definition of a high school gym teacher, down to the ponytail, sneakers, and athletic zip-up hoodie."
    "When her eyes turn from Sibyl toward me, they light up with recognition."
    who "You must be Clover! I'm Miss Woolsey, your athletics instructor!"
    mw "I'm so sorry I couldn't meet you at the gate; time was running short and I had to make this meeting."
    "With some obvious emabrassment, Sibyl chimes in beside me."
    S "I, umm, missed her arrival too. I couldn't sleep at all last night and it caught up with me this afternoon."
    mw "Good thing I asked the royal twins to take my place in delivering the keys."
    mw "I'm sorry that things got so mixed up with your arrival, Clover, but I'm glad you found your way despite that."
    "Our dorm mother isn't as bad as old and crotchety as in the image my mind conjured up, it would seem."
    "In fact, she looks to be rather young, probably barely out of college, and altogether quite pleasant."
    C "(Wait, what did she say? So it was her who sicced those two perverts on me, and they're {b}royalty{/b}?)"
    "Perhaps my consternation may be showing on my face, because the teacher quickly hurries to the heart of the matter when she look back to me."
    mw "How are you settling in, Clover? Was there something you needed to speak with me about?"
    "Before I can shut down Miss Woolsey's good natured assitance, Sibyl jumps in ahead of me."
    S "Well actually... we both entirely missed dinner."
    mw "Is that all? C'mon, let's go raid the kitchen and see what we can find; I'm starving too."
    scene bg black with fade
    scene bg kitchen with dissolve
    "The cooks all seemed to have long ago left for the day when we arrive, but Sibyl and Miss Woolsey manage to scrounge up some peanut butter and jelly for sandwiches."
    "It might not be much of a meal, but I have to admit to myself that it does lighten my mood as well as satisfy my rumbling stomach."
    "The two others accompanying me chat amongst themselves mostly as I try to hang back, but once we're sitting down with sandwiches in hand, it's hard to keep their interest off me for long."
    mw "It is fortunate that you arrived when you did, Clover."
    mw "All the students just came back from their winter breaks so you'll be able to more or less just jump right in as we're picking up steam again!"
    S "But you missed the masquerade ball, which is a pity. It was a lot of fun."
    C "(Masquerade ball? I'm actually thankful I missed {b}that{/b}.)"
    "That I've been staring at the sandwich I'm taking small bites out of should have indicated I don't particuarly care to talk, but it seems these two won't allow that."
    C "Oh yeah?"
    "My reply starts out incredibly half-hearted and disinterested, so I try to raise my enthusiasm just a little to not leave them too dissapointed."
    C "I'm sure I will enjoy studying here, for as long as I stay."
    C "(Oops, didn't meant to say that last part!)"
    mw "I know it must be difficult to transfer in after half the year has already passed, but you'll have your Vertu, Sibyl, by your side every step of the way."
    "The teacher, Miss Woolsey, picks up on my little faux pas easily enough."
    C "(Smarter than the average gym teacher, eh?)"
    "Sibyl nods seriously at what the teacher says, giving me an encouraging smile which only make me look away out of instinct."
    C "That's what Sibyl was telling me."
    "Returning my attention to my sandwich with a chill dismissal, I try to ignore the look that passes between Sibyl and my new teacher."
    mw "Say, if you don't mind me asking, why did you choose to Prudence Prep?"
    C "I didn't {b}choose{/b} to be here. My parents {b}sent{/b} me here."
    C "(Like a loose button that you can't find the sweater it belongs to. Just tossed in a drawer for safekeeping while you go about your life.)"
    "Miss Woolsey, while friendly, is being awfully persistent at trying to get me to open up when I have no intention of doing so, and the annoyance leads me to say more than I wanted to aloud."
    "The room couldn't be getting any chillier if we had left the refrigerator door open."
    "I know I'm acting really terrible, but I have a rightful reason to be this touchy about the subject."
    C "(And it's not like either of them really cares about me anyway.)"
    "It's the teacher's {b}job{/b} to look after me just as much as it is Sibyl's responsibility to be my \"Vertu\"."
    "There's a long silence after I speak where Miss Woolsey's gears are clearly spinning in her head trying to formulate a response to my brusque reply."
    S "Clover, I'm so sorry..."
    "To my surprise, Sibyl reaches without hesitation to lay her hand on my arm and offer her condolences."
    "The soft touch from Sibyl carries a comforting warmth which shocks me for a brief moment. A multitude of emotions swirl through me, from fear to confusion, and anger."
    "I pull away suddenly from her touch reflexively, an action which clearly hurts Sibyl's feelings."
    mw "W-Well... I've long felt like the people here at the academy are a second family to me. So if you ever need anything you can—"
    C "I don't need a second family, I already {b}have{/b} one!"
    "I don't know why I am suddenly feeling this way, but the rush of emotion from the way Sibyl touched me draws you another verbal jab which I cannot take back."
    "It's shockingly ineffective on Sibyl, who only follows my outburst with a look of pity and understanding."
    S "Oh, is that what this is? I understand, Clover..."
    "It's unnerving, to see this strange reaction to me being so cold to her, and it just makes my stomach turn every time I look at Sibyl's consoling smile."
    C "(What could she possibly {b}understand{/b} about any of this? She doesn't even {b}know{/b} me!)"
    "Sibyl might have the expression of clear comprehension on her face, but my athletics teacher is still troubled by everything that's happening."
    mw "I shouldn't have pried into your personal life, Clover, I'm sorry."
    "Surprisingly, she seems mostly down about her own failings than being angry at my rude outbursts."
    C "I-It's fine..."
    "Awkwardly, I try to cool down and smooth things over with the teacher despite Sibyl's strangely calm attitude still being foremost in the jumble of my mind."
    mw "If there's anything you don't feel comfortable talking about with Sibyl, you can always call on me too."
    C "T-Thanks..."
    "I feel like an amoeba under a microscope by the way Sibyl keeps looking at me sympathetically and how Miss Woolsey is thinking through our interaction."
    "Awkwardness permeates the air around me and I just try to focus on finishing my peanut butter and jelly sandwich without thinking about the other two women fretting over my existence."
    C "(When will this day just {b}end{/b}?)"
    scene bg black with fade
    scene bg dormitory with dissolve
    "Finally, we make our way back to the dorms, say good night to the teacher, and get back to our own room."
    "There's a notable difference in the way Sibyl acts toward me now, just a few hours after meeting."
    "She barely demands my attention or says any words beyond what is required. She merely goes about her routine for the night as do I mine."
    C "(What gives? First she wants to be all buddy-buddy and now she's acting all aloof? )"
    "It's kind of infurating actually, that I don't know what she's getting at, and I find myself keep looking back at her as I make my bed and finish my nightly preparations."
    "I keep right on watching her until she starts stripping out of her uniform right in front of me, from which I suddenly jerk my head away fast enough to break my neck."
    C "(Is this normal for roommates?)"
    "Logically, there's nowhere else to change into my sleepwear, so I suffer through the self-consciousness and follow suit."
    S "Good night, Clover."
    "I startle slightly at the suddenly rare sound of her voice floating my direction, and stammer out a short but polite reply of my own."
    "I try my best to brush the half naked form of Sibyl undressing out of my mind as I clamber into my bed for the night."
    "What replaces it is the recollection of what those two girls did to me that late afternoon."
    scene bg black with dissolve
    "Much to my displeasure, I do not manage to come up with any awesome comebacks before I drift off to a restless sleep which fades in an out of the real world around me."
    "At times I'm there sleeping in my dormitory bed, listening to the quiet breathing from the next bed over."
    "Other times I'm trudging down the long tree-lined road to the academy where those two girls, the \"royal twins\", circle around me like vultures with shining gold crowns."
    "Just once, I dream vividly of what those vultures did to me out by the gates. But this time, they're both replaced by my strange new roommate, Sibyl."
    "Her silky chestnut curls flutter around me from either side as she and her double sweep their hands across my body in smooth, sensuous motions."
